{The Bending Tree }
The bending tree was given that name because it was used for bending the metal hoops which were used to put on the wheels of the carts. Outside the forge is a big flat stone . This was used for clamping down the wheels while two blacksmiths put the red hot hoops on with iron tongs.
{Agricultural Use Of Land}
Most of the land in and around Finchdean is pasture and grazing land but there are some crops and potatoes. In the rough grazing there are Charollais and a mixed breed of Friesian and Hereford cows. At the top of{White Hill}there is a group of deciduous trees.
